<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-12-01</DATELINE><TITLE>ER Morphology: Sculpting with XendoU</TITLE><BODY>Endoplasmic reticulum (ER) sheet membranes are covered with ribosomes and RNAs that are involved in protein synthesis. A new study reveals that a calcium-activated endoribonuclease of the EndoU protein family promotes the formation of tubular ER networks, contributing to dynamic shaping of the ER in cells.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>